    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling outing, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 81.88 efficiency score makes him the premier play of the day. Facing R. Nelson, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park adjustment and a 10% boost from his leadoff spot, making him an absolute must-start. **Kyle Tucker** (72.86) also projects as a powerhouse, leveraging a strong xwOBA against the lefty David Peterson, while **Josh Lowe** (65.92) and **Andy Pages** (62.75) provide necessary depth. Notably, **Luis Robert Jr.** (62.21) remains a high-upside play; despite facing a tougher arm in Justin Wrobleski, his stolen base potential is maximized by the pitcher's slow delivery, keeping him in the green despite the overall matchup difficulty.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision today involved **Brady House** (42.28), who barely missed the cut behind **Jacob Wilson** (45.31). While **Brady House** boasts solid platoon splits, the optimizer favored **Jacob Wilson**\u2019s higher projected base efficiency and batting order stability. We are closely monitoring the lineup for **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks**; if either falls lower in the order than our assumed spots, their already marginal scores (54.77 and 52.40) could dip toward the \"Below Floor\" threshold, necessitating a pivot to our bench depth. We are also proceeding with caution regarding **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, as his 53.13 score is heavily suppressed by an 19% penalty against the elite arm of Skenes, and we continue to navigate the absences of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Jordan Westburg** as we manage our active game caps.",
